When creating a new trusted apps link, JIRA suggests some default URL paths to allow:

{noformat}
/sr/jira.issueviews:searchrequest
/secure/RunPortlet
{noformat}

Below in the help text, it says
{quote}List of URL paths (one per line) that the Trusted Application is authorised to access. Must be fully qualified from the Context Path (ie. do not include the base URL).{quote}

Evidently the entered paths match just the beginning of the URL. This is confirmed by the fact that entering '/' causes all URLs to be trusted.

Rather than having this implicit "match everything beginning with" behaviour, we should a) introduce an explicit '*' notation, b) use it for the default paths:
{noformat}
/sr/jira.issueviews:searchrequest*
/secure/RunPortlet*
{noformat}
 This would be consistent with the IP Address Matches field, which uses *'s for wildcards.

